jobs.description:
Joined Lockheed Martin Australia as a Project Systems Engineer in JP2089 Tactical Data Link project based in Canberra. Currently working as Systems Engineering Support to Project Office whilst managing, developing and reviewing Systems Engineering documents towards achieving Design Acceptance from the Design Acceptance Authority based on Navy Technical Regulatory Framework (NTRF) to meet the project milestones. 

Major Contributions:
 Engaging with the internal and external stakeholders to complete the relevant systems engineering activities for the Tactical Data Link Networks utilising my interpersonal skills;
 Developing the experience of operating in Tactical Data Link environment such as the operation of Link 11, Link 16 by liaising with the Subject Matter Experts within the project office and capability development group;
 Managing Design Acceptance activity by coordinating the development of systems engineering management plan, systems specification, engineering drawings, schematics against several Military regulatory standards;
 Managing and undertaking the electrical safety and RADHAZ activities to complete the Safety Case Report of the project.

Managed V&V activities of the integration of Elbit’s Battle Management Systems to the Miltiary vehicles and Maritime Platforms as part of Land 200 and JP2048 programs. Supported systems engineering activities of Land 200 program by undertaking requirement development and analysis, system safety requirement validation. Led Communication, RF, EMC and Grounding test activities of Military Land vehicles of Land 200 program. 

Major Contributions:
	Managed requirement analysis of systems requirements and sub-system & component level requirements towards completion of the detailed design activity and acceptance of the Battle Management Systems;
	Produced Systems Engineering documents by utilising the input from several engineering departments for the completion of successful Functional and Physical Configuration Audits of Battle Management System;
	Developed test plan, test procedures, test reports for the RF, EMC and Grounding test of Battle Management Systems within Military Land  vehicles and Maritime platforms in an efficient and timely manner;
	Performed testing activities related to human factor issues by liaising with other departments regarding the integration of the Battle Management Systems to the Military Land vehicles;
	Accomplished various component level functional testing and verification & validation activities related to the integration of the Battle Management Systems to Maritime platforms within tight deadlines by my proactive interactions with internal and external stakeholders as lead V&V Engineer;
	Completed system safety activities within shorter timeframe due to my excellent analytical skills and effective collaboration with Safety Engineering Manager and external client;
	Conducted RF, EMC and communication engineering investigation and test activities in presence of external stakeholder regarding the radio system integration (HF/VHF/UHF) to the Battle Management Systems within the Military Land vehicles.

Performed requirement analysis, configuration management and systems safety activities of various CBRNE line items whilst maintaining the CBRNE fleet and supported in rapid acquisition of several CBRNE line items. Progressed to work for Systems engineering team in JP2110Ph1B project. Developed and analysed system and sub-system level requirements of several CBRNE line items for the project.

Major Contributions:		
	Developed Functional Performance Specification (FPS) and Operational Concept Document (OCD) liaising with the Capability Development Group (CDG) for JP2110Ph1B project;
	Performed requirement development of system and sub-system level requirements for detection, identification, monitoring of CBRN threats and CBRNE physical protection systems utilising DOORS and MS word collaborating with the external stakeholders;
	Produced System Engineering Management Plan (SEMP), Test and Evaluation Management Plan (TEMP) and Interface Control Plan (ICP) towards the successful completion of the Conceptual Design Review (CDR) of the JP2110Ph1B project;
	Conducted laser safety activities for different laser system within several Defence robots within a very short timeframe by anticipating the difficulty in availability of the relevant laboratory in advance and liaising with the laboratory personnel and obtained laser safety certificate towards completion of the system safety analysis of the robots;
	Developed test procedures and test plans and completed EMC tests as per Military Standards during rapid acquisition of several CBRNE systems by collaborating with the Defence EMC laboratory and troubleshooting Radio Frequency (RF) related issues on those systems;
	Developed and reviewed Engineering Change Proposals using Defence Configuration Management System Teamcentre to successfully obtain Design Acceptance Certificate for CBRNE line items;

Undertook tutorial activities within School of Electrical and Computer Engineering and research activities in High Frequency RF device within RMIT University’s Microwave and Antenna Design Centre.

Major Contributions:
	Tutored, managed and mentored 4th Year and 2nd Year Communication Engineering undergraduate students, and master students from various cultural backgrounds;
	Marked laboratory and tutorial assignments for students and provided face to face verbal and written feedback to the students to enhance the understanding of the subject matter;
	Prepared summary and notes to enhance students’ learning progress;
	Assisted in writing laboratory guides and procedures for the Transmission Line and Microwave Circuit Lab;
	Undertook extensive research and analysis to successfully identifying suitable liquid metal to use in the High Frequency RF coupler;
	Performed electromagnetic simulation to design High Frequency RF device utilising electromagnetic simulation software like Sonnet, HFSS, CST and Agilent Momentum software with a high degree of detail and accuracy;
	Conducted High Frequency measurement utilising Vector Network Analyser, RF Spectrum Analyser etc to verify the simulated results in an efficient manner;
	Published research results in European Microwave Conference and Asia Pacific Microwave Conference.

Worked with clients to build competence in strategic risk management in hazardous industries through:
product stewardship;
sustainable decision making;
environmental, social and economic performance measurement;
leadership and EHS management systems.
